  "body": "The question is already asked on https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/63642/how-to-get-live-mempool-transactions-whitout-full-blokchain and not answered.\r\n\r\nBasically I want to run a node on a cheap VPS server with limited resource that will only give me standard API to request and query the state of `txpool` (how many transactions are there, which is the oldest one, etc.), WebSocket APIs for real-time tracking of transactions leaving and entering the pool, and real-time maintenance API to monitor CPU + memory usage to predict when my node is likely be killed with OOM error, or when it can't catch up with processing incoming transactions.",
